================================================================================
Acknowledgments — Third-Party Components
================================================================================

triforge integrates and re-exposes three independent open-source projects.
All credit for their algorithms, models and source code belongs to the
respective authors and organizations.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. semble — Code search for AI agents
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Project:  https://github.com/MinishLab/semble
   Authors:  Thomas van Dongen  (https://github.com/Pringled)
             Stéphan Tulkens    (https://github.com/stephantul)
   Org:      MinishLab / minish.ai (https://minish.ai)
   License:  MIT
   Used as:  optional MCP server, registered globally and invoked on demand
             by Claude Code. Not bundled, installed via `uvx --from "semble[mcp]"`.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. InsForge — Backend-as-a-Service for AI agents
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Project:  https://github.com/InsForge/InsForge
   Org:      InsForge AI, Inc.
   License:  Apache License 2.0
   Used as:  optional MCP server (cloud or self-hosted Docker). Persistence
             backend for triforge memory when started with `--storage=insforge`.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. HippoRAG 2 — Neurobiologically-inspired GraphRAG
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Project:  https://github.com/OSU-NLP-Group/HippoRAG
   Papers:   "HippoRAG: Neurobiologically Inspired Long-Term Memory
              for Large Language Models" (NeurIPS 2024)
              https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.14831
             "From RAG to Memory: Non-Parametric Continual Learning
              for Large Language Models" (ICML 2025)
              https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.14802
   Org:      OSU NLP Group — Ohio State University
   License:  Apache License 2.0
   Used as:  Python dependency. Powers the chat-memory layer (graph-based
             multi-hop retrieval over conversation history).

